        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://townofcroghan.gov/"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The town and village were named for Colonel George Croghan, a celebrated War of 1812 hero.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        15
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://historicallylewis.org/township_history/croghan/"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "In the 19th century, Croghan boasted a bustling industrial scene with tannery, blacksmith, cheese factory, gristmill, sawmill, and paper mill operations.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        19
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://historicallylewis.org/township_history/croghan/"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Today, Croghan hosts the International Maple Museum and Hall of Fame, celebrating the region’s maple syrup heritage.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        27
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://townofcroghan.gov/"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "The Oswegatchie Educational Center in Croghan offers hands‑on learning about local history and natural resources.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        27
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://townofcroghan.gov/"
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "text": "The Railway Historical Society of Northern New York is headquartered in Croghan, preserving the area’s railroad legacy.",
